  "body": "EVM events are not caught after restoring a saved snapshot of the ganache state during tests with truffle:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nconst { snapshot } = require('@openzeppelin/test-helpers');\r\nconst MyContract = artifacts.require('MyContract');\r\ncontract(\"MyContract\", function (accounts) {\r\n  before(async () => {\r\n    this.myContract = await MyContract.deployed();\r\n    this.snapA = await snapshot();\r\n  })\r\n  it(\"should work\", async () => {\r\n   await myContract.throwEvent(); // <-- event is shown during `truffle test --show-events`\r\n  })\r\n  it(\"should work too\", async () => {\r\n   await this.snapA.restore();\r\n   await myContract.throwEvent(); // <-- event is NOT shown during `truffle test --show-events`\r\n  })\r\n});\r\n```\r\nHowever, checking the transaction receipt manually has the logs set up with the event data in question.\r\n\r\nTested with:\r\n\r\nTruffle v5.5.0 (core: 5.5.0)\r\nGanache v7.0.1\r\nSolidity - 0.8.11 (solc-js)\r\nNode v16.14.0\r\nWeb3.js v1.5.3",
